A two-year-old girl has died in hospital days after her stepfather shook her until she suffered a brain hemorrhage, police said.

Thaiya Spruill-Smith was rushed to Brookdale Hospital in Brooklyn, New York, on Thursday after her 24-year-old mother Teoka Spruill noticed she was struggling to breathe.

Despite numerous operations, doctors last night concluded Thaiya's head injuries were too severe to overcome, and she was taken off life support.

